       ] ;
       fhir:value [
         a fhir:Markdown ;
         fhir:v "Because serious Hib disease occurs most commonly in children aged 4–18 months, immunization \n  should start from 6 weeks of age, or as early as possible thereafter. The interval between doses should \n  be at least 4 weeks if 3 primary doses are given. Hib-containing vaccine is not required for healthy \n  children aged over 5 years."
       ]
